InnerClass
----------
    --> Collection of both homogenous/heterogenous data elements
    --> Cotains properties and behaviour

    --> class within another class
    --> 3 different categories
            -- Member InnerClass:

                    Ex: 
                        class Outer{
                            int data;
                            class MemberInner{

                            }
                        }

                        Outer objOuter = new Outer();
                        MemberInner objMemberInner = objOuter.new MemberInner();

            -- Local InnerClass:

                    Ex:
                        class Outer{
                            int data;
                            void localInnerDemo(){
                                class LocalInner{ 
                                }
                            } // scope of LocalInner class
                        }

            -- Anonymous InnerClass
                    - Creating an object wihout any name inside another object
                    Ex:
                        btnAdd.addActionListner(new newActionListener({
                                // object is created without its name
                        }));
